gomodel:SYNGO_3928  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Tsc2+/- hippocampal pyramidal neurons transfected at DIV 21 with EGFP showed immature spines ( more long, thin filopodia) compared the WT. Quantification showed the Tsc2 mutation reduced the width of dendritic protrusions and increased their length.. Experimental description: 24/09/2018 Pim\n- \"In this study, we used spontaneous Tsc2-mutated Eker rats as animal models of TSC11. We first compared dendritic spine morphology of cultured hippocampal neurons of wild type (WT) and heterozygous Eker (Tsc2+/-) rats. At 21 days in vitro (DIV), the dendritic spines of WT neurons displayed mushroom-type spines (Fig. 1a)(top), whereas the dendrites of Tsc2+/- neuron\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2094-7491" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9848-0262" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4419-210X" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1190-4481" ;
        dc:date           "2018-09-24" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_3928" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

